	It has been a long while since I have read, from start to finish,
"Infinity and the Mind" by Rudy Rucker.  I was, however, skimming through
it the other day, and I noticed what I think is a contradiction.  It is
located in my paperback version on p. 86, last paragraph.  That would be
chapter two, section 3, Infinitesimals and Surreal Numbers.

	"I would respond that omega is a _given_, an object of our
immediate pre-rational experience.  And to use the tools of symbolic logic
to investigate an _empirically_ existing phenomenon..."

